baseContent.title: üå∑ B3 | Greenhouse
baseContent.description:
The smell of fresh herbs, flowers, fruits and vegetables fills the Greenhouse. It is considerably hotter inside the Greenhouse than the rest of Garreg Mach. Large windows surround the building, allowing in as much natural light as possible for the plants to blossom and bloom.

The Greenhouse Keeper stands in the middle of the Greenhouse and smiles at you as you enter. In the corner, looking at some roses, is Dorothea.

baseContent.title: üõèÔ∏è C3 | Dormitory
baseContent.description:
Tucked away in a quieter wing of Garreg Mach Monastery, the Commoner Dormitories offer simple yet functional living quarters for students. Students lounge on the lawn outside or come and go from their rooms throughout the day - and night.  On the lawn, a beagle sits sadly. He appears to want something he does not have. 

You hear scuffling coming from Bernadetta's room - the room she so rarely leaves.

Underneath one of the trees appears to be a book. It has been left out in the sun for a few hours now and the pages have been earmarked in multiple places.

baseContent.title: ‚öîÔ∏è D3 Officers Academy
baseContent.description:
The Officers Academy has a sprawling grass common area where students relax and enjoy the sun. Some are studying while others relax and enjoy the sun. It is a busy area indeed, and items are scattered about. Interestingly, you see a bone laying underneath a tree.

Across from the grassy common area are three large wooden doors. Each door has it's own flag - Black Eagles, Blue Lions, and Golden Deer. The flags move slightly in the soft wind that blows. You note that by each flag seems to be the house leader. Edelgard is deep in conversation with Hubert, however would likely talk to you if you went over. Claude is sitting on the ground with his eyes closed, bent towards the sun. Dimitri stands at attention, watching each passing student - and you - carefully.

baseContent.title: ‚õ™ E3 Cathedral
baseContent.description:
Six pillars support the looming ceiling of the Cathedral. To the side, you can hear students practicing with the Choir Coordinator - and someone is certainly off key. An incredibly tall window sits at the end of the Cathedral allowing in the bright sunlight of the day. Illuminated by the sunlight, looking out through the window, is Rhea.

To the side is a small room with the four Saint Statues. You see that Mercedes is praying at one now.

baseContent.title: üêü B4 | Fishing Pond And Dining Hall üçΩÔ∏è
baseContent.description:
Nestled beside the greenhouse and quietly humming with the scent of wet stone and algae, the pond's surface glimmers with the occasional ripple. Nearby, a weathered stone ledge offers a perch for weary students or eager anglers

Half-submerged in the shallows is a Fishman. He wears a faded cap, mutters to the koi, and seems far more interested in conversation than catching anything.

Near the edge, just beneath a crooked reed and half-covered in moss, lies a small bundle of bait. It‚Äôs unclear who left it, but it looks just tempting enough to take.

---------------------------------------------

Across from the Fishing Pond is the Dining Hall. Students are spready across various tables enjoying the meal of the day and sharing stories. The Head Chef stands near the food, talking to students about cooking tips. At one of the tables, Raphael is enjoying a large plate of food by himself.

baseContent.title: üèõÔ∏è C4 Reception Hall
baseContent.description:
The Reception Hall has large, looming ceilings with windows that allow the light to shine through onto the tiled floor. Large chandeliers hang above benches where students mingle and discuss the day. Their candles flicker lazily. On one of the tables sits a snapped writing quill.

At one of the tables sits Sylvain. He appears to be stressed about something. At the end of the hall pacing back and forth is Ignatz, carrying something in his hand.

baseContent.title: üìç D4 | Knight's Hall
baseContent.description:
The Knight‚Äôs Hall stands as a testament to discipline and tradition‚Äîits stone walls lined with crossed lances, crested shields, and banners from campaigns long past. Polished training dummies and sparring mats fill the center, while the scent of oiled leather and steel hangs in the air.

Veteran knights murmur strategy over maps or hone blades beside the hearth, their armor clinking with every deliberate movement. A sense of quiet readiness permeates the space, as though every figure within could be summoned to battle at a moment‚Äôs notice.

Sitting in the corner is a figure who very much stands out amongst the Knights. Hilda's pink hair flips as she laughs at something one of the Knights has said to her. On the table behind them sits a coin purse... ripe for the taking if someone wants it.

baseContent.title: üåâ E4 | Bridge to Cathedral
baseContent.description:
> Stretching across a wide chasm beneath Garreg Mach Monastery, the bridge is a majestic span of pale stone lined with carved balustrades and weather-worn statues of saints and wyverns.
> 
> Moss creeps up between the flagstones, hinting at the age of the structure, while fluttering banners in House colours catch the wind overhead.
> 
> Though there are no shifts in elevation, the sheer length of the bridge gives it a feeling of ceremonial grandeur‚Äîas though crossing it is a rite in itself. 

The Gates are currently sealed shut. There's a tough looking, well armored guard at base of the gates. Leaning against the edge of the bridge and looking out across the horizon is Ashe. Across from him is Annette, who is painting the brilliant blues of the sky and dotting white clouds on canvas.

baseContent.title: üõí B5 Marketplace
baseContent.description:
The Marketplace is a bustling centre with different vendors to choose from and different wares to purchase. Here, you can get anything from weapons, to herbs and vegetables, to gifts! All for the right price. One student you recognize right as you enter, as you see Petra is looking at some of the vegetables at a stall.

On the steps to the building Flayn is sitting with her head in her hands.

baseContent.title: üö™ C5 Entrance Hall
baseContent.description:
The Entrance Hall - the great hub for all comings and goings of Garreg Mach. Here, families and students alike get their first look at inside the monestary. Large blue doors swing open to reveal a tiled floor and pillars supporting the roof - a room large enough that if no one were here, you could hear the echo of a pin drop.

Leaning against one of the walls is Ingrid, who appears to be deeply engrossed in her book. Across from her is Lysithea, who is currently admiring one of the paintings on the walls.

baseContent.title: üêé D5 | Stable
baseContent.description:
The Stables are ripe with noise and energy as horses neigh and hit against their stables, demanding attention or apples - or both. Marianne is talking to one of the horses now, softly petting it's mane while she whispers something to it that you can't make it. 

To the side, Ferdinand dismounts from a black horse and waves to you.

baseContent.title: ‚öîÔ∏è E5 Training Grounds
baseContent.description:
Weapons clash against each other and training dummies as students practice their different skills in the Training Grounds. Arrows fly past, shooting their targets. 

Caspar is in the middle of the training grounds mid duel with Felix. Leonie watches on the side, her eyes following the moves of the two fighters carefully.

Seteth stands near the edge of the area pacing. He seems to be deep in thought.

config.title: The Fisherman Smiles
config.content:
Ahhh, you've got the wrigglers, do ya? That‚Äôs the stuff. Fish round here don‚Äôt bite without a proper offering. Toss a line in and see what bites back. Just... don‚Äôt look ‚Äôem in the eyes.

The fisherman looks at you like he wants to ask you something...

config.title: The Fisherman Doesn't Have time for you..
config.content: No bait, no bites. That‚Äôs the law of the pond. Same as it ever was. Course, the clever ones say the worms find you... but that‚Äôs just pond talk.

config.title: Blech! Baitt!
config.content: You plunge your hand into the slimy moss, and scoop up a bunch of bait.. whatever it is. You slip it into your inventory.

enquire_to_see_what__876806.label: Enquire to see what he wants..

config.title: Someone's got a crushh....
config.content:
> "Er, you didn‚Äôt see me lookin‚Äô her way, did you? It‚Äôs just... well, Lady Edelgard passed by here the other day and‚Äîah, never mind."

[He clears his throat and hastily holds up a slightly bruised apple.]

Fisherman:
"Think you could give her this? It‚Äôs not much, but it‚Äôs... shiny. Like her armor. Tell her it‚Äôs from... a friend of the fish."
(He looks away awkwardly.)

talk_to_knight_412024.label: Talk to Knight

config.title: You talk to the Nervous Knight
config.content:
"Oh! Uh... hello! I wasn‚Äôt‚Äîwell, I mean, I was stationed here, I just‚Äîlisten, this is awkward."

(He clears his throat and tries to stand at attention. It doesn't help.)

"I was told not to move until someone gives me the uh... the secret code."

(He winces, already regretting this.)

Nervous Knight:
"Sooo... if you know it, great. If not, maybe try typing in that little ‚Äîthe `/menu` slash command? Then `‚å®Ô∏è Enter Command`. Maybe it‚Äôll come to you."

(He avoids eye contact, clearly hoping you don‚Äôt ask too many questions.)

tags: Coy knight that wants you to guess the secret code.

talk_to_sylvain_760859.label: Talk to Sylvain

config.title: Sylvain Ask
config.content: "Hey Professor. Funny seeing you here. You're looking lovely as ever. Think you could help me out with something? Dorothea asked me to meet her at the Greenhouse so we could go over to The Goddess Tower. Yeah - where lovers meet. I don't have the heart to tell her I'm not interested like that. Could you tell her for me? Just say those exact words. *Sylvain is not interested.* Thanks Professor."

config.title: Sylvain Rejected
config.content: She doesn't want to...? Oh! I see. Well uh... thank you for the notes Professor. Oh man, I wish I could just disappear for 24 hours and not have to talk to anyone - I'm so embarrased.

config.title: Ferdinand Gives Gold
config.content: Hello professor. Isn't it a lovely afternoon? I have some spare gold in my pocket - why don't you take it for me? Get some tea.

config.title: Dorothea is Rejected
config.content: Wait Sylvain didn't think - oh my GOODNESS Professor absolutely not. I might be looking to marry somebody, but I certainly was not asking Sylvain to. I just wanted to give him some notes he missed at seminar. Can you take them for me instead?

config.title: Speak to Ignatz
config.content: Oh hey Professor! I'm glad I ran into you. I was supposed to go to the Greenhouse today to plant these tomato seeds, but I promised Raphael I'd try and spar with him! Can you do it for me?

config.title: No Seeds
config.content: You have no seeds to plant

config.title: Pie Please?
config.content: "Oh h..hi Professor... How are you today?" Marianne pauses. "I - Professor... can I ask you a favor? I do not want to leave Avel here... but I am so hungry. Can you make me a Garreg Mach Meat Pie? You just need *Wild Game, Tomato, and Cabbage*.

config.title: Marianne is Thankful
config.content: "Thank you Professor! I - thank you. Please take this to use as a token of my appreciation."

config.title: Speak to Edelgard
config.content: Edelgard smiles at you as you approach. "Hello Professor. I hope you are well today. It seems that Garreg Mach is quite lively today. Here - take this. Perhaps you can get something at the Marketplace that you like or would be helpful in future battles."

config.title: Hello Professor
config.content: Edelgard nods politely at you. "Good day, Professor."

config.title: Hey Teach
config.content: Almost as if he hears you approach, Claude's eyes open and look at you. He flashes you a grin. "Hey Teach, what a beautiful day out today, isn't it? Hey ya know what - why don't you swing by the Marketplace and get your something something? My treat." Claude reaches into his pocket and hands you some gold coins.

config.title: Hey Teach
config.content: Almost as if he hears you approach, Claude's eyes open and look at you. He flashes you a grin. "Hey Teach, what a beautiful day out today, isn't it? Hope you have a good one." Claude closes his eyes and seems to return to his... slumber? You aren't too sure he's really sleeping.

config.title: Hello Professor
config.content: Dimitri smiles as you approach him. "Ah, Professor. It is lovely to see you today. I had to take a break from my training today to rest, but I hope you are enjoying your time around Garreg Mach." Dimitri reaches into his pocket and hands something over to you. "Here. I saw that there are some new things in the Marketplace recently. Perhaps something will catch your eye."

config.title: Hello Professor
config.content: Dimitri nods to you as you approach. "Hello Professor. I hope you are well today." He then turns his attention back to the other students.

config.title: Give a Dog a Bone
config.content: The dog perks up as you approach it for pets, and quickly runs to your pocket where you had previously put a bone. It excitedly begins to bark at you. You pull at the bone and hand it over to the dog. The dog barks with joy and runs off for a moment before returning, dropping Wild Game at your meet.

config.title: He Wants More
config.content: The dog leans into your hand as you pet him. He seems happy but... he wants more. There must be something out there that could make this dog happy.

config.title: A... A gift?
config.content:
Bernadetta squeals loudly as you knock on the door. "No no no no no," you hear from the other side of the door. After a moment, the door opens just a crack - enough for Bernadetta to poke her head through and look at you. "Yes Professor? Is everything okay? Did I do something wrong? OH I DID SOMETHING WRONG DIDN'T IT?" As Bernadetta begins to back away, you pull out the Pitcher Plant you bought earlier and present it to her.

Bernadetta's hands reach out to grab the plant and you see her smile before her eyes widen. "No no no no no Professor I can't accept this gift! This must have cost you so much money. Oh no no no no." Bernadetta throws gold coins at your feet before slamming the door closed behind her.

config.title: Scared Bernadetta
config.content: Bernadetta squeals loudly as you knock on the door. "No no no no no," you hear from the other side of the door. After a moment, the door opens just a crack - enough for Bernadetta to poke her head through and look at you. "Yes Professor? Is everything okay? Did I do something wrong? OH I DID SOMETHING WRONG DIDN'T IT?" Bernadetta slams the door shut behind her, retreating back inside.

config.title: I'm busy, Professor
config.content: Hubert eyes you as you approach him and Edelgard. "Hello Professor. I am rather busy right now. Perhaps you should visit Bernadetta. I believe she has locked herself in her room again. Perhaps a plant might coax her out. She is rather fond of them."

config.title: Missing Ingredients
config.content: You do not have all the necessary ingredients to cook a meal right now

config.title: I Have An Idea
config.content: Seeing you approach, Caspar quickly drops his fighting stance and runs over to you. "Hey, Professor! Just the person I wanted to see. I was thinking - we should do a tournament! Some of our best fighters in a battle to see who comes out on top. I was thinking me, Raphael, Ingrid, Hilda, and  Petra. I'm busy right now, but can you talk to them and get them to agree?"

config.title: Wow
config.content: "Thanks so much Professor! That fight was *amazing*. I can't believe Hilda won. Here - she told me to give you this. Said she was too tired to carry it around, but maybe you could use it?"

Petra looks at you as you approach to speak with her. "Hello Professor. It is lovely to be seeing you here on today. I am very busy looking for fruit from my homeland, but they do not carry it. One day, I hope to bring much of the food from Brigid to here."

config.title: Oh?
config.content:
Petra looks at you as you approach to speak with her. "Hello Professor. It is lovely to be seeing you here on today." 

You tell Petra that Caspar would like to hold a tournament, and that she is invited. Petra smiles widely. 

"Oh yes! I would most loving to be doing that Professor. Tell Caspar I am happy to fight."

config.title: No Greens!
config.content: "I just wanna eat meat and fish, but everyone in the dining hall says I gotta eat vegetables too! I'm never gonna get full on some stupid leaves!" You hear Raphael complain as he eats his meal. It appears to be an incredibly large plate of meat, with no single vegetable on it.

config.title: A Fight? I'm in!
config.content:
"I just wanna eat meat and fish, but everyone in the dining hall says I gotta eat vegetables too! I'm never gonna get full on some stupid leaves!" You hear Raphael complain as he eats his meal. It appears to be an incredibly large plate of meat, with no single vegetable on it.

You sit at the table across from Raphael and tell him about Caspar's idea.

"A fight? I'm in! Tell Caspar I'm there anytime, Professor."

config.title: A Good Book
config.content: Ingrid does not seem to notice your approach until you are standing beside her. She jumps a little when she notices you. "Sorry Professor. I was reading a book of Pegasus Knights. I have always admired Pegasus Knights for the versatility they bring to battle. I was thinking I might focus my studies there. I was also thinking that I need a snack soon with all this reading."

config.title: I love to train!
config.content:
Ingrid does not seem to notice your approach until you are standing beside her. She jumps a little when she notices you. "Sorry Professor. I was reading a book of Pegasus Knights. I have always admired Pegasus Knights for the versatility they bring to battle."

You tell Ingrid about Caspar's idea and she quickly closes the book. "I'd love to join, Professor! Those boys don't know what's coming for them."
"Hi Professor, I'm busy right now. Maybe we can talk later?"
"Why Professor, that sounds so exciting? But don't you think you would be so much better at it than me? Professor? Oh fine! I'll do it!"

config.title: Hello, you
config.content: Rhea smiles warmly at you as you approach. "Hello, you. How are you enjoying the Monestary so far? Have you prayed at the Saint Statues today? Please - take some money for your time here."

config.title: Can You Tell...
config.content: "Hi Professor!" She smiles as you approach, waving you over. I am so glad you were here. I was looking at this painting and I thought - wow, this guys buttons like of look like mini cakes! And I was thinking that Felix might like some cake. Can you tell him that? Tell Felix *The buttons look like Cake*. Thank you!"

Felix rolls his eyes when you tell him what Lysithea said. "I'm training and that is what she wants to tell me? There must be someone else who that would interest." Felix looks around the training grounds. "Perhaps Leonie. Tell Mercedes *The buttons are cake*. Now I have to get back to this."

config.title: Saint Cethleann Statue
config.content: ‚ÄúA statue of Saint Cethleann, one of the Four Saints. It is said that she was a beautiful and kind soul who was beloved by all for her empathy and her ability to heal severe wounds. She is the daughter of Saint Cichol.‚Äù

config.title: Saint Cichol Statue
config.content: ‚ÄúA statue of Saint Cichol, one of the Four Saints. It is said that he was a compassionate yet stern figure whose faith was so true he was able to perform miracles. He is the father of Saint Cethleann.‚Äù

config.title: Saint Macuil Statue
config.content: ‚ÄúA statue of Saint Macuil, one of the Four Saints. It is said that his gift for strategy was unparalleled. He served as chief tactician of Saint Seiros and was a pioneering figure for and master of the magical arts.‚Äù

config.title: Saint Indech Statue
config.content: ‚ÄúA statue of Saint Indech, one of the Four Saints. It is said that he was known for his wisdom and dexterity. Though unskilled in the art of human interaction, he used his gifts to help those in need. He was also an indomitable warrior who slew countless foes on countless battlefields.‚Äù

config.title: Thank you!
config.content: Thank you! I have been looking for this for ages!

config.title: Oh Hey
config.content: Sorry I'm trying to remember where I left something.

config.title: I Can't Remember...
config.content: Sorry I know Flayn asked me for something but I‚Äôm so distracted from my missing item.

config.title: You Found My Quill!
config.content: Ohmygosh thanks so much. Now I remember, Flayn needed my help to get a fish! Can you help her?

tags: ‚ÄúSorry I know Flayn asked me for something but I‚Äôm so distracted from my missing item."

config.title: You Can't...
config.content:
You don't have anything to cast with.
Try again when you have the proper tools!

config.title: Cast and Wait
config.content:
You cast your rod out into the water and wait.
Soon your bobber dips and you catch a fish!

config.title: Hmph...
config.content: I asked Seteth to help me with something. But I think he forgot.

config.title: A Herring!
config.content:
Oh! Seteth didn't forget!
Thank you for bringing this to me for him!

config.title: What was that?
config.content: "Oh hello Professor! I'm sorry - it's very loud in here. I can't quite hear you. What was that? Felix is a glutton? For cake? Oh! I am sure that Annette would like to hear about this. Can you please go and tell Annette that *Felix is a glutton for cake*? Thank you!"

Annette looks up from her painting as you approach and tell her about Felix. You see a giant grin spread across her face. "Is he professor? You must tell Lysithea at once! She will be so happy to here. Please, go tell Lysithea *Felix is a cake glutton*."

phrases: Felix is a glutton for cake
Felix is a Glutton for Cake

config.title: Is He?
config.content:
Lysithea stops as you tell her about Felix. "Is he Professor? Oh I have to get him some cake right now! He would love something sweet. Here - hold onto this for me while I get one." 

**Ping Production in your submissions to see if Lysithea has anything for you**
